63void VCMFrameBuffer::SetGofInfo(const GofInfoVP9& gof_info, size_t idx) {
64 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "VCMFrameBuffer::SetGofInfo");
65 _sessionInfo.SetGofInfo(gof_info, idx);
66 // TODO(asapersson): Consider adding hdr->VP9.ref_picture_id for testing.
67 _codecSpecificInfo.codecSpecific.VP9.temporal_idx =
68 gof_info.temporal_idx[idx];
69 _codecSpecificInfo.codecSpecific.VP9.temporal_up_switch =
70 gof_info.temporal_up_switch[idx];
71}

73// Insert packet
74VCMFrameBufferEnum VCMFrameBuffer::InsertPacket(const VCMPacket& packet,
75 int64_t timeInMs,
76 const FrameData& frame_data) {
77 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "VCMFrameBuffer::InsertPacket");
78 assert(!(NULL == packet.dataPtr && packet.sizeBytes > 0));
79 if (packet.dataPtr != NULL) {
80 _payloadType = packet.payloadType;
81 }
82
83 if (kStateEmpty == _state) {
84 // First packet (empty and/or media) inserted into this frame.
85 // store some info and set some initial values.
86 SetTimestamp(packet.timestamp);
87 // We only take the ntp timestamp of the first packet of a frame.
88 ntp_time_ms_ = packet.ntp_time_ms_;
89 _codec = packet.codec();
90 if (packet.video_header.frame_type != VideoFrameType::kEmptyFrame) {
91 // first media packet
92 SetState(kStateIncomplete);
93 }
94 }
95
96 size_t oldSize = encoded_image_buffer_ ? encoded_image_buffer_->size() : 0;
97 uint32_t requiredSizeBytes =
98 size() + packet.sizeBytes +
99 (packet.insertStartCode ? kH264StartCodeLengthBytes : 0);
100 if (requiredSizeBytes > oldSize) {
101 const uint8_t* prevBuffer = data();
102 const uint32_t increments =
103 requiredSizeBytes / kBufferIncStepSizeBytes +
104 (requiredSizeBytes % kBufferIncStepSizeBytes > 0);
105 const uint32_t newSize = oldSize + increments * kBufferIncStepSizeBytes;
106 if (newSize > kMaxJBFrameSizeBytes) {
107 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to insert packet due to frame being too "
108 "big.";
109 return kSizeError;
110 }
111 if (data() == nullptr) {
112 encoded_image_buffer_ = EncodedImageBuffer::Create(newSize);
113 SetEncodedData(encoded_image_buffer_);
114 set_size(0);
115 } else {
116 RTC_CHECK(encoded_image_buffer_ != nullptr);
117 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(encoded_image_buffer_->data(), data());
118 encoded_image_buffer_->Realloc(newSize);
119 }
120 _sessionInfo.UpdateDataPointers(prevBuffer, data());
121 }
122
123 if (packet.width() > 0 && packet.height() > 0) {
124 _encodedWidth = packet.width();
125 _encodedHeight = packet.height();
126 }
127
128 // Don't copy payload specific data for empty packets (e.g padding packets).
129 if (packet.sizeBytes > 0)
130 CopyCodecSpecific(&packet.video_header);
131
132 int retVal = _sessionInfo.InsertPacket(
133 packet, encoded_image_buffer_ ? encoded_image_buffer_->data() : nullptr,
134 frame_data);
135 if (retVal == -1) {
136 return kSizeError;
137 } else if (retVal == -2) {
138 return kDuplicatePacket;
139 } else if (retVal == -3) {
140 return kOutOfBoundsPacket;
141 }
142 // update size
143 set_size(size() + static_cast<uint32_t>(retVal));
144
145 _latestPacketTimeMs = timeInMs;
146
147 // http://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_ts/126100_126199/126114/12.07.00_60/
148 // ts_126114v120700p.pdf Section 7.4.5.
149 // The MTSI client shall add the payload bytes as defined in this clause
150 // onto the last RTP packet in each group of packets which make up a key
151 // frame (I-frame or IDR frame in H.264 (AVC), or an IRAP picture in H.265
152 // (HEVC)).
153 if (packet.markerBit) {
154 rotation_ = packet.video_header.rotation;
155 content_type_ = packet.video_header.content_type;
156 if (packet.video_header.video_timing.flags != VideoSendTiming::kInvalid) {
157 timing_.encode_start_ms =
158 ntp_time_ms_ + packet.video_header.video_timing.encode_start_delta_ms;
159 timing_.encode_finish_ms =
160 ntp_time_ms_ +
161 packet.video_header.video_timing.encode_finish_delta_ms;
162 timing_.packetization_finish_ms =
163 ntp_time_ms_ +
164 packet.video_header.video_timing.packetization_finish_delta_ms;
165 timing_.pacer_exit_ms =
166 ntp_time_ms_ + packet.video_header.video_timing.pacer_exit_delta_ms;
167 timing_.network_timestamp_ms =
168 ntp_time_ms_ +
169 packet.video_header.video_timing.network_timestamp_delta_ms;
170 timing_.network2_timestamp_ms =
171 ntp_time_ms_ +
172 packet.video_header.video_timing.network2_timestamp_delta_ms;
173 }
174 timing_.flags = packet.video_header.video_timing.flags;
175 }
176
177 if (packet.is_first_packet_in_frame()) {
178 playout_delay_ = packet.video_header.playout_delay;
179 }
180
181 if (_sessionInfo.complete()) {
182 SetState(kStateComplete);
183 return kCompleteSession;
184 }
185 return kIncomplete;
186}

213void VCMFrameBuffer::Reset() {
214 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "VCMFrameBuffer::Reset");
215 set_size(0);
216 _sessionInfo.Reset();
217 _payloadType = 0;
218 _nackCount = 0;
219 _latestPacketTimeMs = -1;
220 _state = kStateEmpty;
221 VCMEncodedFrame::Reset();
222}
223
224// Set state of frame
225void VCMFrameBuffer::SetState(VCMFrameBufferStateEnum state) {
226 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "VCMFrameBuffer::SetState");
227 if (_state == state) {
228 return;
229 }
230 switch (state) {
231 case kStateIncomplete:
232 // we can go to this state from state kStateEmpty
233 assert(_state == kStateEmpty);
234
235 // Do nothing, we received a packet
236 break;
237
238 case kStateComplete:
239 assert(_state == kStateEmpty || _state == kStateIncomplete);
240
241 break;
242
243 case kStateEmpty:
244 // Should only be set to empty through Reset().
245 assert(false);
246 break;
247 }
248 _state = state;
249}
250
251// Get current state of frame
252VCMFrameBufferStateEnum VCMFrameBuffer::GetState() const {
253 return _state;
254}
255
256void VCMFrameBuffer::PrepareForDecode(bool continuous) {
257 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "VCMFrameBuffer::PrepareForDecode");
258 size_t bytes_removed = _sessionInfo.MakeDecodable();
259 set_size(size() - bytes_removed);
260 // Transfer frame information to EncodedFrame and create any codec
261 // specific information.
262 _frameType = _sessionInfo.FrameType();
263 _missingFrame = !continuous;
264}
